NAME
    format - convert JSON to various output formats

SYNOPSIS
    format <type>
    cat data.json | format <type>
    select * FROM users | format csv

DESCRIPTION
    Converts JSON input from stdin to the specified output format.
    Uses the @monk/formatter-* packages for encoding.

    Input must be valid JSON. For tabular formats (csv, markdown),
    input should be an array of objects.

FORMATS
    csv         Comma-separated values (for spreadsheets)
    markdown    Markdown table (aliases: md, table)
    toml        TOML configuration format
    toon        Token-Oriented Object Notation (compact for LLMs)
    grid        Compact grid format (alias: compact)
    cbor        Concise Binary Object Representation (base64 output)
    msgpack     MessagePack binary format (base64 output)
    qr          QR code as ASCII art
    morse       Morse code
    brainfuck   Brainfuck encoding (just for fun)

EXAMPLES
    select * FROM users | format csv
        Export users as CSV

    select * FROM products | format markdown
        Display products as a markdown table

    select * FROM config | format toon
        Convert to TOON (30-60% fewer tokens for LLMs)

    cat data.json | format qr
        Generate QR code from JSON

    select name, email FROM users | format csv > users.csv
        Export specific fields to file

NOTES
    Binary formats (cbor, msgpack) output base64-encoded data.

    For CSV and markdown, input should be an array of flat objects.
    Nested objects will be JSON-stringified.

EXIT STATUS
    0   Success
    1   Error (invalid JSON, unsupported format, encoding error)

SEE ALSO
    jq, select, cat
